==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Brog
<hw>Brog</hw> <pr>(br⟦ocr⟧g)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gael. Cf.
<er>Brob</er>.]</ety> <def>A pointed instrument, as a joiner's awl, a
brad awl, a needle, or a small sharp stick.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brog</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Brog
<hw>Brog</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To prod with a pointed instrument,
as a lance; also, to broggle.</def> <mark>[Scot. & Prov.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brogan</ent>⟦br⟧
